<div class="jumbotron py-4 mb-3">
  <h1 class="display-4">FFXIV Collect</h1>
  <p class="lead">Another website for tracking your Final Fantasy XIV collections.</p>
  <hr class="my-4">
  <h5>Keep your Lodestone collections updated automatically</h5>
  <p>
    Your collections are updated automatically to reflect any new mounts, minions, and achievements you obtain
    based on your Lodestone profile.
  </p>
  <h5>Update the rest with a simple user interface</h5>
  <p>
    Any collectables not visible on your Lodestone profile can be updated manually as you obtain them.
  </p>
  <h5>Do you have feedback? I want to hear it!</h5>
  <p>
    The community is what motivates me to create these projects, so if you have any feedback,
    let me know on <%= link_to 'Discord', 'https://discord.gg/Bf62wNU', target: '_blank' %>.
  </p>
  <div class="mt-4 text-center">
    <%= link_to 'Discuss on Discord', 'https://discord.gg/Bf62wNU', class: 'btn discord mt-2', target: '_blank' %>
    <%= link_to 'Support on Patreon', 'https://www.patreon.com/raelys', class: 'btn patreon mt-2', target: '_blank' %>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12">
    <div class="card">
      <h5 class="card-header">API</h5>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p>
          All of the data used on this site is available for any savvy developers through a public RESTful JSON API.
          You can check out the full documentation
          <%= link_to 'here', 'https://github.com/mattantonelli/ffxiv-collect/wiki', target: '_blank' %>.
        </p>
        <b>GET <%= link_to nil, api_mount_url(186), class: 'unstyled' %></b>
        <%= render 'api_sample' %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
